<section id="section-about" data-bgcolor="#853f40">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="row align-items-center">
                <div class="col-md-7 offset-md-3 text-center wow fadeInUp">
                    <h2 class="heading-with-underline">Our &nbsp;Founder </h2>
                    @*<div class="separator"><span><i class="fa fa-square"></i></span></div>
                    <div class="spacer-single"></div>*@
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4 text-middle wow fadeInLeftBig">
                    <img src="~/Content/web/images/founder.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="" style="margin-top: -10px;">
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-1"></div>
                <div class="col-md-7 wow fadeInRightBig text-middle">
                    <p class="lead" style="font-size:40px;">

                        Major General Raghubir Singh Pannu

                    </p>
                    <p class="lead">
                        After an illustrious Army career General Raghu Pannu  took over as the Director General of Helpage India. .Under his dynamic leadership he took the little known fledgling NGO, and put it  on the map as Indias leading charity and soon age care became synonymous with Helpage India.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lead">
                        General Pannu's dedication to the cause and stellar performance won him much acclaim.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-12">
                    <p class="lead">
                        He served on the Governing Boards of the World Fundraising Council and CASP, was the Founder Chairman of  SAARC ,Trustee of Child Fund India , Patron of Rehablitation India and Treasurer General and Vice president of the International federation of Aging in Canada    He was also on the Advisory Board of  leading International charities such as Help the Aged UK, Helpage International , Global Cancer Concern UK,
                   
                        British Executive Services Overseas and the Prince of Wales Business Leaders Forum UK
                        In recognition of his achievements the DISTINGUISHED LEADERSHIP AWARD was conferred upon him by the American Biographical institute. He was also the receipient of IFA's PRESIDENTS AWARD  for the most outstanding contribution worldwide in the field of Age care in 2000.
                        Gen Pannu was honoured with the KARAMVEER PURUSKAR by the Indian Confederation Of NGOs , posthumously .

                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


